==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fishhawk
<hw>Fish"hawk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The osprey (<spn>Pandion halia⟦eum⟧tus</spn>), found both in Europe
and America; -- so called because it plunges into the water and seizes
fishes in its talons. Called also <altname>fishing eagle</altname>, and
<altname>bald buzzard</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fishhook</ent>⟦br⟧
